OL,6,F"It was frightening. All our dishes
OL,7,Fmoved. We have to prepare the children
OL,8,Fto not be scared, but they are going
OL,9,Fto be scared," she said.
OL,11,F"My child goes to school 134 metres
OL,12,Ffrom this fence. She'll go back end of
OL,13,FAugust. They're going to start
OL,14,Fblasting in October, and my child has
OL,15,Fsaid to me, 'When is that school going
OL,16,Fto fall down on me?'"
OL,18,FClaire says others in the community
OL,19,Fare losing a part of their childhood
OL,20,Fas the mountain around the quarry is
OL,21,Fcordoned off.
