OL,6,F"The blast at Craig-yr-Hesg quarry
OL,7,Flast Monday (05 August) was carefully
OL,8,Fdesigned by specialists to minimise
OL,9,Fground vibration. This was to mitigate
OL,10,Fimpact on the local community and the
OL,11,Flow blast vibration levels
OL,12,Fsubsequently recorded were well within
OL,13,Fthe permitted limits.
OL,15,F"Air overpressure (AOP) can be
OL,16,Fresponsible for the noise associated
OL,17,Fwith blasts ` and it is often the
OL,18,Fmovement of air and not vibration that
OL,19,Fis felt. AOP is also carefully
OL,20,Fcontrolled, including for last
OL,21,FMonday's blast.
